GfxInfo (console command)
=========================

Description
-----------

Reports OpenGL version, extensions found, rendering paths enabled and other graphics card related information.

Usage
-----

At the console type...

`gfxinfo`

Parameters
----------

This console command does not accept parameters.

Notes
-----

You can use this command to see which rendering paths are potentially available in your video card for use with the [r\_renderer](R\_renderer\_(cvar)) CVar.


